<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-01-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-01-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="208" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d208">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian
                                    Pauncefote</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">British
                                        Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-01-28"><hi rend="italic">January 28,
                                1892</hi></date>. (Received January 28.)</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 22d instant transmitting the decision of the
                            Treasury Department in regard to the case of John Gibbons.</p>
                        <p>I should be very much obliged if you would convey my best thanks to the
                            Acting Secretary of the Treasury for the courteous attention which has
                            been paid to my request, and at the same time inform him that I have
                            forwarded a copy of his letter to my Government.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Julian
                            Pauncefote.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>